        "text": "# Best Angel Investors in the World\n\nHere are some of the most successful and influential angel investors globally:\n\n## Top Tier Angel Investors\n\n### 1. **Marc Andreessen**\nCo-founder of [Andreessen Horowitz](https://a16z.com/) and Netscape. Early investor in Facebook, Twitter, Airbnb, and many other successful startups.\n\n### 2. **Naval Ravikant**\nFounder of [AngelList](https://www.angellist.com/). Invested in over 200+ companies including Uber, Twitter, Yammer, and Postmates.\n\n### 3. **Ron Conway**\nFounder of [SV Angel](https://svangel.com/). Known as the \"Godfather of Silicon Valley,\" with early investments in Google, Facebook, PayPal, Twitter, and Airbnb.\n\n### 4. **Peter Thiel**\nCo-founder of [PayPal](https://www.paypal.com/) and [Palantir](https://www.palantir.com/). First outside investor in Facebook and invested in SpaceX, LinkedIn, Yelp, and Stripe.\n\n### 5. **Reid Hoffman**\nCo-founder of [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/). Early investor in Facebook, Airbnb, and numerous other startups through [Greylock Partners](https://greylock.com/).\n\n## Other Notable Angel Investors\n\n### 6. **Elad Gil**\nVP at Twitter, invested in Airbnb, Coinbase, Instacart, Pinterest, Square, and Stripe. Author and advisor. [Personal site](http://blog.eladgil.com/)\n\n### 7. **Chris Sacca**\nFounder of [Lowercase Capital](https://lowercasecapital.com/). Early investor in Twitter, Uber, Instagram, and Kickstarter.\n\n### 8. **Esther Dyson**\nExecutive founder of [Wellville](https://wellville.net/). Early investor in Flickr, del.icio.us, Evernote, and 23andMe.\n\n### 9. **Dave McClure**\nFounder of [500 Startups](https://500.co/). Invested in over 2,000 companies including Credit Karma, Twilio, and Wildfire.\n\n### 10. **Jason Calacanis**\nFounder of [LAUNCH](https://launch.co/). Early investor in Uber, Robinhood, and Calm. Host of the podcast \"This Week in Startups.\"\n\n## International Angel Investors\n\n### 11. **Yuri Milner**\nFounder of [DST Global](https://dst-global.com/). Major investments in Facebook, Twitter, Airbnb, and Spotify.\n\n### 12. **Li Ka-shing**\nThrough [Horizons Ventures](https://www.horizonsventures.com/), invested in Facebook, Spotify, Zoom, and Impossible Foods.\n\n### 13. **Masayoshi Son**\nFounder of [SoftBank](https://www.softbank.jp/en/). Early investor in Yahoo, Alibaba, and through Vision Fund.\n\n## Key Resources\n\n- [AngelList](https://www.angellist.com/) - Platform connecting startups with angel investors\n- [Crunchbase](https://www.crunchbase.com/) - Database for researching investors and their portfolios\n- [Forbes Midas List](https://www.forbes.com/midas/) - Annual ranking of top tech investors\n- [CB Insights](https://www.cbinsights.com/) - Research on venture capital and angel investing trends\n\nThese investors are known for their track records, the quality of companies in their portfolios, and their ability to add value beyond just capital through mentorship, connections, and strategic guidance.",
